criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. sample information is complete, including sample number, gender, age and clinical
             diagnosis;

          2. CRC group: positive samples refer to samples confirmed to be CRC with colonoscopy
             and/or pathological examination;

          3. precancerous disease group: all samples confirmed to be adenoma and polyps by
             colonoscopy and/or pathological examination

          4. other disease group: samples confirmed to be other GI diseases, other cancers or no
             evidence of diseases by colonoscopy and/or pathological examination

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. the patient information is not complete;

          2. the sample information is not complete;

          3. history of colorectal cancer surgery or other cancer history, or any chemotherapy;

          4. women in pregnancy;

          5. samples not comply with any of the above selection criteria
